    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, the social stuff is important for the context. but for the actual data part, can u just break down what the specific trends show? like, for some of the major groups, what are the actual recorded differences in arrest rates or crime statistics? i need the raw numbers/trends to build the foundation of my paper before i start layering in the systemic explanations.",
